Module com.bcs2024.knapsack
Package com.bcs2024.knapsack.algorithm.dancinglinks

Class DancingLinks

java.lang.Object
com.bcs2024.knapsack.algorithm.dancinglinks.DancingLinks
public class DancingLinks extends Object
Implements the Dancing Links algorithm for solving exact cover problems, specifically applied to the context of a knapsack problem. The class primarily focuses on arranging parcels in a cargo space to maximize the total value while considering the cargo dimensions.

  • Method Details

    • AddRow

      public void AddRow(int row, int pentId, int[] ones, int[][][] piece)
      Adds a row to the sparse matrix representation of the exact cover problem. Each row represents a way to cover part of the matrix.
      Parameters:
      row - The row number in the matrix.
      pentId - The unique identifier for the pentomino.
      ones - Array of column indices in this row where the matrix has 1s.
      piece - The 3D shape of the piece being placed in the cargo space.

    • algorithmX

      public void algorithmX(int step)
      Implements Algorithm X, a recursive backtracking algorithm to solve the exact cover problem. It progressively covers columns of the matrix by choosing rows that have non-empty cells in those columns. This process effectively explores potential solutions, backtracking when a partial solution cannot be extended to a complete one.
      Parameters:
      step - The current step or depth of the recursion, used to track the progress of the algorithm.

    • addParcelInfoToList

      public void addParcelInfoToList(ParcelInfo parcelInfo)
      Adds parcel information to the list of parcelInfoList. This information is used to track the details of the parcels placed in the cargo space.
      Parameters:
      parcelInfo - The ParcelInfo object containing details about the parcel.

    • cover

      private void cover(Header head)
      "Covers" a column header in the matrix, effectively removing the column and all rows linked to it from the matrix. This is part of the process to recursively solve the exact cover problem.
      Parameters:
      head - The header of the column to be covered.

    • uncover

      private void uncover(Header head)
      "Uncovers" a previously covered column header in the matrix, effectively reinserting the column and all linked rows back into the matrix.
      Parameters:
      head - The header of the column to be uncovered.
